  "texts": [
    "Medical data processing on the edge and in the cloud both involve administrators, endangering patient privacy.",
    "BCT used in conjunction with the Fig. 3 Edge devices as a bridge between IoT devices and Cloudcloud and edge devices may make it possible to process and store patient data without depending on centralized cloud management [42,43].",
    "The BCT's decentralized and distributed nature makes it fundamentally different from conventional databases.",
    "Using \"blocks,\" which are collections of data, a BCT may securely store large amounts of data in a distributed ledger (DTL).",
    "The basic architecture of Blockchain is depicted in Fig. 4 Researchers have developed various privacy-preserving eHealth solutions as a result of the Blockchain's structure."
